title: Bernie Ecclestone expects full F1 grid in 2016 amid Red Bull... - Hampshire Chronicle
text:
Formula One chief executive Bernie Ecclestone insists there will be a full quota of teams on the grid next season despite mounting uncertainty surrounding Red Bull's future. Red Bull, who won four consecutive driver and team titles between 2010 and 2013, have threatened to quit the sport if they cannot find a competitive engine supplier for next year.
 Hampshire Chronicle.
